# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Source of truth + history — COMMITTED (NOT ignored; no pattern below matches them):
#   docs/  PLAN.md  genesis.tasks.json  AGENTS.md  CLAUDE.md  project-context/
# A committed stale .map/ would lie to the next clone (the failure freshness-stamping
# exists to prevent); a git-ignored genesis.tasks.json would lose the backlog. Keep the
# split exact.
# NOTE: .gitignore has NO inline/trailing comments — every pattern is alone on its line
# (a trailing "# ..." becomes part of the pattern and silently breaks the ignore).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Derived / rebuildable / local — never commit (regenerated on demand):
#   .map/      project map, rebuilt by tools/project-map/build.py
#   .genesis/  genesis receipts, interview log, calibration snapshot
#   .refiner/  prompt-refiner calibration
.map/
.genesis/
.refiner/

# code-review's own policy: commit suppressions.json + standards.md; ignore the rebuildable:
.review/index.json
.review/outcomes.jsonl

# design-creator's own policy: ignore ONLY the heavy mockup iterations:
.design/mockups/

# Language / tooling noise:
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
node_modules/
.DS_Store
